subtitle: [Music]
television has become what sleep is like
to us
an integral part of our lives with the
vast variety of
cheap attractive and entertaining
content it allows
we turn a blind eye to its negative
aspects
television simultaneously disrupts our
life activities
makes us violent lazy numb and sets
unrealistic goals for us at the same
time small
children experience a huge negative
impact
be it on their mental health or their
physical health
a general problem with today's society
and its prevalent problems
like laziness a tendency to be violent
and
anxiety can be attributed to the
widespread negative influence of
television on modern society studies
have proven
that most teenagers and young adults
nowadays watch
more than three hours of television in
one day
if compared to the ones who watch
television for less than one hour daily
they are more than twice as likely to
commit an act of violence
in their near future according to the
researchers of this study
the link between tv and aggressive
behavior
is as strong as the link between smoking
and
lung cancer when it comes to violence
the younger generations today are
exposed to a lot of violent actions
from a very tender age it can be in the
form of movies
tv series and even children's cartoon
shows
the children as well as some adults have
a tendency of worshiping these violent
action characters and heroes
they often end up trying to imitate
their violent behavior
in order to appear more likeable and
cool
in front of their peers television has a
bigger impact on small
children it decreases their
concentration span
when they watch a tv program they need
to concentrate for only a few minutes
before it is interrupted by an
advertisement
when watching a tv program they do not
have to use much of their imagination
or think critically as compared to
reading books
the scenarios are conveniently played
out to them it reduces their cognitive
powers
additionally there are many health
problems related to sitting in front of
a tv screen for long periods
whenever we turn on the television to
watch the news it is evident that a vast
majority of it
is bad news almost to the point that
more than 70 percent of the news
is bad news of wars famine accidents
scandals and other crimes this leads to
a belief in people that committing some
kind of an offense
or attacking someone will bring them
fame
while the crime rates all over the world
have significantly raised over the years
television has a way of covering these
crime stories
as interesting stories or documentaries
movies and series more often than not
end up portraying the criminals
as some sort of a genius and
misunderstood
mastermind someone to be sympathized
with
a human being by his nature is a species
who thrives to achieve
more and more wealth and materialistic
things
when we watch the advertisements on the
television we see
attractive products like electronics
cars
branded clothes food jewelry and so much
more
they are portrayed to us in a way that
makes us believe that we cannot live
without them
it creates a desire in our brain and
when we realize we cannot afford these
products
we have a feeling of inferiority we get
jealous and angry when we see our
friends
show offing the said product so we end
up going
out of our way to purchase that
extravagancy or in worst scenarios we
may try to steal the product
we may commit a crime it is a scientific
fact that what comes
in our contact is bound to influence our
behavior
we regularly watch violent tv shows with
crimes like murder
assault abuse or suicide it eventually
negatively impacts our attitude
and brain processes in the long run our
conscience gets
numbed and we become bystanders when we
see criminal offenses
like animal abuse or theft in our real
lives
we may end up becoming indifferent even
to devastating events of death
and suicides we become numb after having
spent hundreds of hours of our lives
watching television every experience be
it comedy
travel documentaries reality tv criminal
files
and even porn has been covered by you
no human experience can excite you
anymore
the innocent excitement and happiness
that you once felt
has been killed by television television
makes you lazy it has become an
essential to us
we simply cannot imagine our life
without it
hundreds of millions of people around
the globe sit down
every single day and spend hours
bringing on their favorite tv shows
we are so obsessed with it that we may
even spend hours watching
programs that we may not even like do we
see this happening anywhere else
of course nobody spends hours watching a
baseball game if they do not like
baseball
but we will watch bad tv for hours on
end
just because we love tv so much
the hours we spend behind the screen
just sitting there and maybe
occasionally getting up to get some
snacks
makes us dangerously unhealthy we keep
on procrastinating on all
important tasks of life while
prioritizing television
going to take a walk outside seems like
a big challenge
because we have spent so much time
sitting in our rooms with a numb mind
doing absolutely nothing and by the time
realization hits that we are out of
shape
and need to quit the unhealthy practices
as soon as possible
we are already spiraling way too deep
down the rabbit hole
to get back up while television sets
unrealistic goals of achievements and
happiness in our lives
we become more and more demotivated and
unsatisfied with our own lives a common
trope of tv shows
is showcasing their characters as ultra
rich people with posh
lifestyles even the poor characters
become rich
overnight by overcoming minor problems
and by watching these shows we tend to
forget that the road to success
starts from achieving small milestones
the prospect of having a life like the
characters seems so hard that we give up
without even trying
the rabbit hole of television is never
ending
imagine you just settled in your cozy
bed or sofa
with your favorite snacks and a nice
drink and put on a good tv show
you may convince yourself that you have
important work tomorrow
you will watch this one episode and go
to sleep
but how many times do we keep on
endlessly repeating the same thing
we keep on pressing on the watch next
episode button
and wake up with two hours of sleep the
next day
we become tired and irritated for the
whole rest of the next day
compromise with our work performance and
regret the decision of the previous
night
but do we really learn and this does not
end here
tv programs intentionally end their
episodes as well as series with
cliffhangers
to keep you hooked so instead of having
a feeling of satisfaction after
finishing watching one season
or an episode of a show you will feel
unsatisfied and thirsty for the next one
you are never truly satisfied tv
watching
is an endless loop it is high time that
we change this destructive habit
before it gets too late
